### PetFind API requests (used by the frontend)
# Define base URL (ajuste se seu backend rodar em outra porta/host)
@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000

# -- Auth ------------------------------------------------------------------

### Register user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Seu Nome",
  "email": "you@example.com",
  "password": "s3cret",
  "telefone": "1199999-9999",
  "cidade": "Brasilia",
  "estado": "DF",
  "foto": "data:image/jpeg;base64,/..."  # opcional: base64 ou URL dependendo do backend
}

### Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "you@example.com",
  "password": "s3cret"
}

### Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/logout

### Get current user (me)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/me
# withCredentials/cookie required when running from browser

# -- Pets ------------------------------------------------------------------

### List pets
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/pets

### Create pet (JSON example)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/pets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Fido",
  "raca": "SRD",
  "idade": 2,
  "sexo": "macho",
  "cidade": "Brasilia",
  "estado": "DF",
  "mainPhoto": "https://.../foto.jpg"  # ou envie multipart/form-data
}

### Create pet (multipart/form-data example)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/pets
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary

------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="name"

Fido
------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="mainPhoto"; filename="fido.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./path/to/fido.jpg
------WebKitFormBoundary--

### Update pet
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/pets/:petId
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Fido atualizado",
  "idade": 3
}

### Delete pet
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/pets/:petId

# -- Likes / Matches / Messages --------------------------------------------

### Like a pet (creates like / possibly match)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/pets/:toPetId/like
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromPetId": "ID_DO_SEU_PET"
}

### List matches (conversations)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/matches

### List messages in a match
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/matches/:matchId/messages

### Send message in a match
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/matches/:matchId/messages
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "Olá!"
}

# Notes:
# - Substitua `:petId`, `:toPetId` e `:matchId` pelos IDs reais.
# - As chamadas do frontend usam cookies (withCredentials). Quando testar via REST Client,
#   você pode precisar autenticar com /api/auth/login e copiar o cookie de sessão, ou
#   configurar variáveis de autorização conforme seu backend (JWT, cookie, etc.).
